OL,3,CFive per cent council tax hike in
OL,4,CPlymouth as leader promises to 'turn
OL,5,Cthe tide'
OL,7,FPlymouth City Council's Conservative
OL,8,Fleader, Cllr Andy Shayer, said more
OL,9,FGovernment money is needed as soon as
OL,10,Fpossible - otherwise the taxpayer will
OL,11,Fcontinue to bear the burden.
OL,13,F"Quite simply, we cannot possibly
OL,14,Fallow a situation where these services
OL,15,Faren't delivered," Cllr Shayer said.
OL,17,F"The way forward with any budget is
OL,18,Fcan you get any extra money in. Well,
OL,19,Fthere is a funding gap. The government
OL,20,Fhasn't delivered the money which we
OL,21,Fexpected to see.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/9
